Azure Landing Zones are preconfigured environments designed to support scalable, secure cloud adoption.

They include:

* Governance
* Identity
* Networking
* Security baselines

For example, enterprises establish landing zones before migrating large workloads.

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is structured enterprise cloud transformation.

# Real-Life Example:
Another example is multinational organizations standardizing deployments.

Landing Zones accelerate secure cloud adoption.
